  "text": "A similar non-injection and low temperature approach was also used for PbS QD synthesis [CITATION_1] . The obtained PbS QD has a bandgap emission from 600 to 900 nm with a narrow emission FWHM of 100 nm. Different lead and sulfur sources have been used including lead oxide, lead acetate, bis(trimethylsilyl)sulfide ((TMS)2S), thioacetamide (TAA), and elemental sulfur (S). ODE is used as a reaction medium, and the reaction temperature is 30-120°C.",
